==English==
===Noun===
'''lecithin'''
{{wikipedia}}

# the principal [[phospholipid]] in animals; it is particularly abundant in egg [[yolk]]s, and is extracted commercially from [[soy]].  It is a major constituent of [[cell]] [[membrane]]s, and is commonly used as a [[food additive]] (as an [[emulsifier]]).
===Synonyms===
*[[phosphatidylcholine]]
*[[E322]] when used as an [[emulsifier]]